other_tests.findings: Normal spontaneous phasic flow and compressibility within the right internal jugular, axillary, brachial and cephalic veins. A PICC line is visualized within the right basilic vein, which demonstrates a normal spontaneous flow. There is a spontaneous phasic flow within the right subclavian vein. A vessel is identified in the area of previous IV placement in the right wrist. No flow is identified within this vessel and there is subcutaneous edema in this region.
